<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-07-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-07-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="192" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d192">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Choate</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-07-09"><hi rend="italic">July 9,
                                1901</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 668.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 599 of the 21st ultimo, inclosing copy of a note from the foreign
                            office suggesting that the Government of the Kongo Free State be
                            notified that His Britannic Majesty’s consul at Boma has been authorized
                            to take charge of American interests there.</p>
                        <p>You will inform the foreign office that this has been done.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>